x4freetext: Detailed analysis of
measurements and  experimental details
3.75  MV Van de Graaff  Accelerator
pulse width is less than 1 ns, repetition rate
250 kHz, average beam current 1.7  microAmp
Metallic Li target of about 1 mg/cm2
Flight path is 78.8 cm, resolution 0.5 ns/m
Single target irradiation
Karlsruhe 4PI-Ba-F2 detector consisting of
42 hexagonal and pentagonal crystals forming
a spherical Ba-F2 shell of 15 cm thickness and 10 cm
inner radius. Resolution is 7% at 2.5 MeV gamma
energy, peak efficiency  90 % at 1 MeV
.Proton beam energy adjusted so to be 30 and 100 keV
above the 7-Li(P,N)7-Be reaction threshold 1.881 MeV
giving neutrons in energy ranges 3-100, 3-225 keV
.Standard gold sample Au-197, three 0.125 mm thick
disks 8, 10, and again 8 mm diameter inside the
Titanium spheres perpendicular to the neutron beam.
Gold sample weight is 441.0 milligram, Ti sphere
weight is 3.1434 gram
.Graphite sample 157.7 milli-gram weight, enclosed in
Titanium sphere 3.1363 gram
.Empty Ti spheres for background measurements
.Corrections were made for multiple scattering,
for isotopic impurities, for neutron self-absorption,
for undetected events, for signal/background ratio -
all for different neutron energies
Last checking has been done.
SD: EN-MEAN -> KT and all values were
corrected in Subents 008-011. ERR-ANALYS moved to
Subents 2-11.
Averaged over
energy interval given in data section
.Absolute measurement
.Xenon gas enclosed in titanium sphere. Mass 368 and
478 milligram, Titanium spheres weights are 3.01 and
3.02 gram.  Xe-124 content is less than 0.01%,
Xe-126 content is  0.04%, Xe-128 content is 99.6 %,
Xe-129 content is  0.39%, Xe-130 to Xe-136 content is
less than 0.01%
Data are taken from Table 5 of PR/C,66,064603
Total error
Total systematic error includes:
Error due to flight path uncertainty
Error due to neutron flux normalization
Error due to sample mass and elemental
impurities
Error due to isotopic composition
Error due to multiple scattering and self-
shielding
Error due to undetected events
